<DOC><DOCNO> AP881006-0258 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-06-88 0857EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Taiwan-Trade     10-06 0140</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Taiwan-Trade,0147</SECOND><HEAD>Taiwan's Trade Surplus Declines</HEAD><DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Taiwan's trade surplus totaled $1.04billion in September, down 27 percent from the previous month anddown 54 percent from the same month a year ago, the governmentreported Thursday.   The Directorate General of Budget, Accounting and Statisticssaid exports in September totaled $4.47 billion, down 22 percentfrom the previous month, while imports were $3.43 billion, a 20percent decrease from August.   The agency said Taiwan registered a total surplus of $7.82billion for the first nine months of this year, down 48 percentfrom the same period last year. Against the United States, Taiwan'sbiggest trading partner, the surplus totaled $992.6 million inSeptember, down 22 percent from August.   Trade officials attributed the decline of imports and exportspartly to the four-day Mid-Autumn Festival holiday in September.</TEXT></DOC>